Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
title: Investigation of proton channel for decay of giant resonance for the nucleus S-32.

x4freetext: Investigation of proton channel for decay of giant

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.28, p.302 (1978)

x4freetext: was obtained by evaporation on polyethylene foil,
The spectra of photoprotons from the S-32 nucleus are
measured in the bremsstrahlung beam. The upper limit
of the bremsstrahlung spectrum was varied from 17 to
30 MeV in shorter than 1-MeV steps. The spectra are
used to calculate the distribution of transition to
different states of the residual nucleus P-31 and to
determine the corresponding partial photoproton cross
Two duplicate data lines in SUBENT 2 data section
SD: Updated to lower case. Corrected
according last EXFOR rules and Dict.
Ref. on transl. was added. BIB update.
